write, 1 tool result + final response).\",\"-\",\" ## Verification\",\" \",\" ```bash\",\" mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\",\" ```\",\" \",\"-Then manually test with the real Kiro test repo:\",\"-1. Run a Kiro session in `/Users/alisha/Projects/test-repos/kiro-aws`\",\"-2. Check that `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt` contains the user prompts\",\"-3. Check that `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/summary.txt` contains the last assistant response\",\"+Then test in the Kiro IDE with an empty repo — the stop hook should exit 0 with no error.\"]}],\"originalFile\":\"# Plan: Implement TranscriptAnalyzer for Kiro Agent\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe Kiro agent doesn't implement the `TranscriptAnalyzer` interface, causing `prompt.txt` and `summary.txt` to always be empty in checkpoints. The lifecycle handler (`lifecycle.go:233`) skips prompt/summary/file extraction when this interface isn't implemented. Claude Code and Gemini CLI both implement it — Kiro should too.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Action |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/types.go` | Add transcript data types |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/transcript.go` | **New** — parse helpers and constants |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/kiro.go` | Add 4 TranscriptAnalyzer methods |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle.go` | Add compile-time interface assertion |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/kiro_test.go` | Update compile-time assertion block |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/transcript_test.go` | **New** — table-driven tests |\\n\\n## Reference: Gemini CLI pattern\\n\\nFollow `geminicli/transcript.go` + `geminicli/gemini.go:201-277` + `geminicli/lifecycle.go:16` as the reference implementation. Kiro's format is similar (single JSON blob) but uses paired history entries instead of a flat messages array.\\n\\n## Kiro Transcript Format (from real SQLite cache)\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"conversation_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\",\\n  \\\"history\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"user\\\": { \\\"content\\\": { \\\"Prompt\\\": { \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"text\\\" } }, \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"...\\\" },\\n      \\\"assistant\\\": { \\\"Response\\\": { \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"text\\\" } }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"user\\\": { \\\"content\\\": { \\\"Prompt\\\": { \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"text\\\" } } },\\n      \\\"assistant\\\": { \\\"ToolUse\\\": { \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\", \\\"tool_uses\\\": [\\n        { \\\"id\\\": \\\"tu-1\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"fs_write\\\", \\\"args\\\": { \\\"path\\\": \\\"/abs/path/file.go\\\", ... } }\\n      ]}}\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"user\\\": { \\\"content\\\": { \\\"ToolUseResults\\\": { \\\"tool_use_results\\\": [...] } } },\\n      \\\"assistant\\\": { \\\"Response\\\": { \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Done.\\\" } }\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n- Position = `len(history)` (each entry is a user+assistant pair)\\n- User content is tagged union: `Prompt` or `ToolUseResults`\\n- Assistant content is tagged union: `Response` (text) or `ToolUse` (tool calls)\\n- File modification tool: `fs_write` (observed), `fs_edit` (defensive)\\n- Tool args: `path` field has absolute paths\\n\\n## Implementation Steps\\n\\n### 1. Add transcript types to `types.go`\\n\\nUnexported types (package-internal, following existing pattern):\\n\\n- `kiroTranscript` — top-level: `conversation_id` + `history []kiroHistoryEntry`\\n- `kiroHistoryEntry` — `user kiroUserMessage` + `assistant json.RawMessage`\\n- `kiroUserMessage` — `content json.RawMessage` + `timestamp string`\\n- `kiroPromptContent` — for unmarshalling `{\\\"Prompt\\\": {\\\"prompt\\\": \\\"...\\\"}}`\\n- `kiroToolUseContent` — for unmarshalling `{\\\"ToolUse\\\": {...}}`\\n- `kiroResponseContent` — for unmarshalling `{\\\"Response\\\": {...}}`\\n- `kiroToolUsePayload` — `message_id`, `tool_uses []kiroToolCall`\\n- `kiroResponsePayload` — `message_id`, `content`\\n- `kiroToolCall` — `id`, `name`, `args json.RawMessage`\\n\\nUse `json.RawMessage` for the tagged unions (user content, assistant content, tool args) — try each variant in helpers rather than custom UnmarshalJSON.\\n\\n### 2. Create `transcript.go` with parse helpers and constants\\n\\nFile modification tools constant:\\n```go\\nvar kiroFileModificationTools = []string{\\\"fs_write\\\", \\\"fs_edit\\\"}\\n```\\n\\nPure functions (no methods on KiroAgent):\\n- `parseTranscript(data []byte) (*kiroTranscript, error)`\\n- `extractUserPrompt(content json.RawMessage) string` — returns prompt text or \\\"\\\"\\n- `extractModifiedFilesFromHistory(entries []kiroHistoryEntry) []string` — deduped file paths\\n- `isFileModificationTool(name string) bool`\\n- `extractFilePath(args json.RawMessage) string` — checks `path`, `file_path`, `filename`\\n- `extractLastAssistantResponse(entries []kiroHistoryEntry) string` — walks backward for last Response\\n\\n### 3. Add TranscriptAnalyzer methods to `kiro.go`\\n\\nAll four methods on `*KiroAgent`, following the Gemini pattern (read file → parse → extract):\\n\\n- **`GetTranscriptPosition(path)`** → `len(t.History)`, return 0 for missing/empty/`{}`\\n- **`ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(path, startOffset)`** → slice `t.History[startOffset:]`, extract file paths via `extractModifiedFilesFromHistory`\\n- **`ExtractPrompts(sessionRef, fromOffset)`** → iterate `t.History[fromOffset:]`, collect `extractUserPrompt` results\\n- **`ExtractSummary(sessionRef)`** → `extractLastAssistantResponse(t.History)`\\n\\n### 4. Add compile-time assertion\\n\\nIn `lifecycle.go` (matching Gemini's `lifecycle.go:16`):\\n```go\\nvar _ agent.TranscriptAnalyzer = (*KiroAgent)(nil)\\n```\\n\\nUpdate `kiro_test.go:16-19` to add the assertion there too.\\n\\n### 5. Add tests in `transcript_test.go`\\n\\nTable-driven tests with `t.Parallel()` and `t.Run`:\\n\\n- `TestParseTranscript` — valid, empty history, `{}`, invalid JSON\\n- `TestExtractUserPrompt` — Prompt variant, ToolUseResults variant, empty\\n- `TestExtractModifiedFilesFromHistory` — fs_write paths, non-file tools skipped, dedup\\n- `TestGetTranscriptPosition` — empty path, missing file, empty file, placeholder `{}`, normal\\n- `TestExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset` — offset 0, offset > 0, offset >= len, missing file\\n- `TestExtractPrompts` — all prompts, with offset, skips ToolUseResults entries\\n- `TestExtractSummary` — last Response, skips ToolUse, empty transcript\\n- `TestExtractFilePath` — path field, file_path fallback, filename fallback, empty\\n\\nUse a shared `testKiroTranscript` constant with 4 history entries (2 prompts, 1 tool use with fs_write, 1 tool result + final response).\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nThen manually test with the real Kiro test repo:\\n1. Run a Kiro session in `/Users/alisha/Projects/test-repos/kiro-aws`\\n2. Check that `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt` contains the user prompts\\n3. Check that `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/summary.txt` contains the last assistant response\\n\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"8d857c0e-919c-4b29-8c2a-38fc777cfe50\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c605ed1f-a322-4547-b22d-7b8b9d5686db\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"8ff7050d-1d9f-42fa-9893-4a3ce065bc04\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"recursive-giggling-reef\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01SfPt4zqJ3BBwrBHo51bxYN\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_016ytDm91TN5JZbQq5TrzR5e\",\"name\":\"ExitPlanMode\",\"input\":{\"plan\":\"# Plan: Fix Kiro IDE stop hook exit code 1 on empty repos\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nAfter the TranscriptAnalyzer changes and the stdin fix (d01bbc6a), the Kiro IDE stop hook now progresses further in the execution path — far enough to hit the empty repository check in `handleLifecycleTurnEnd`. This check returns `NewSilentError(strategy.ErrEmptyRepository)`, which causes `os.Exit(1)` in `main.go:44-45`. The Kiro IDE reports this as \\\"Hook execution failed with exit code 1. No output was captured.\\\"\\n\\nThis is a regression: the stop hook should exit 0 when skipping an empty repo, since it's a benign skip condition (not an error).\\n\\n## Root Cause\\n\\n`cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:179-181`:\\n```go\\nif repo, err := strategy.OpenRepository(ctx); err == nil && strategy.IsEmptyRepository(repo) {\\n    logging.Info(logCtx, \\\"skipping checkpoint - will activate after first commit\\\")\\n    return NewSilentError(strategy.ErrEmptyRepository)  // ← causes os.Exit(1)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n`cmd/entire/main.go:44-45`:\\n```go\\ncancel()\\nos.Exit(1)  // ← any non-nil error, including SilentError, triggers exit code 1\\n```\\n\\n## Fix\\n\\nChange `lifecycle.go:181` from `return NewSilentError(strategy.ErrEmptyRepository)` to `return nil`.\\n\\nThe log message already communicates the skip. Returning nil gives exit code 0, which is the correct behavior for a hook that successfully decided \\\"nothing to do.\\\"\\n\\n## File to Modify\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:181` | `return NewSilentError(...)` → `return nil` |\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nThen test in the Kiro IDE with an empty repo — the stop hook should exit 0 with no error.\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":619,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":83455,\"output_tokens\":38,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":619,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYh229we4SxvKJMj6Lfvk\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"8f2d7238-20aa-4e2